A Crypto Fort Knox, NWSL Fantasies, The Watch-Collecting Renaissance
--------------------------------------------------------------------

Happy Monday and welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon
compendium of Puck=E2=80=99s best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Leigh Ann Caldwell probes House Democrats=E2=80=99 inner di=
alogue as they face this week=E2=80=99s vote on Mike Johnson=E2=80=99s Trum=
p-endorsed bill to avoid a government shutdown. In true Democratic fashion,=
 the party is wrestling with itself over how to proceed=E2=80=94and whether=
 approving the bill would be perceived by voters
as endorsing Elon Musk=E2=80=99s chainsaw approach to dismantling the feder=
al agencies.

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Dylan Byers digs into David Shipley=E2=80=99s auto-de=
fenestration from The Washington Post amid Jeff Bezos=E2=80=99s editorial s=
hake-up. Bill Cohan contemplates Trump=E2=80=99s quixotic Fort Knox=E2=80=
=93style Strategic Bitcoin Reserve.
Julie Davich profiles Dimepiece founder Brynn Wallner, the woman single-han=
dedly reshaping the traditionally buttoned-up world of watch collecting. An=
d Sarah Shapiro offers a tactical assessment of T.J. Maxx=E2=80=99s retail =
